Shadow Wing::

She was whistling an old Cybertron tune as she finished welding on 
the sheet metal to the hull.  she turned off the torch and looked at 
her handiwork. "Hmm, not bad" she looked down the rest of the hull. 
she gave a long sigh and hung her head. There was just so much to 
do.  she just hoped that there was enough time to get it all done in. 
She put the torch down and went for another sheet.  She saw there was 
only large scraps left.  She picked it up and looked to see where it 
might fit best.
